# Drop your TLS material here in production:
#
#   cert.pem   PEM-encoded leaf certificate; concatenate intermediate /
#              root CA chain *after* the leaf if your corporate CA isn't
#              already trusted by clients.
#   key.pem    Matching unencrypted private key (PKCS#8 or PKCS#1).
#
# These files are mounted read-only into the Caddy container at
# /etc/caddy/certs/ and never copied into the image. They are gitignored
# below so a key never leaks into git history by accident.
#
# Keep root-only / 600 permissions on the host.

cert.pem
key.pem
chain.pem
fullchain.pem
*.crt
*.key
*.pfx
*.p12
